 Kernel

ğŸ’­What is Kernel?

ğŸ‘‰Central component of OS     
ğŸ‘‰Manages operations of computer and H/w
ğŸ‘‰Acts as a bridge between Applications & data-processing performed at H/W level



ğŸ’­What are Different Types of Kernel present?

ğŸ‘‰Windows and Windows Phone uses NT Kernel
ğŸ‘‰OS10 and iOS uses Darwin kernel
ğŸ‘‰Android uses Linux Kernel



ğŸ’­Types of Kernels

ğŸ‘‰Monolithic Kernels - Linux is a monolithic Kernel.
All the services, all drivers, all things handling memory all are present in one program that occupies one memory space.

ğŸ‘‰Microkernel - Kernel takes very small memory space & others- like device drivers, networking and file systems runs as user level programs & kernel interacts with them. 
If one of those crashes, Kernel doesn't

